Method Detail

extrude

public UGeometry extrude(UGeometry obj,
                         float inset,
                         float extrusion,
                         boolean isWindow)
Creates an extruded version of all quads stored in a UGeometry instance, given inset and extrusion factors. Optionally, the isWindow parameter can be set to true to leave the front face of the extruded geometry open, producing a window effect.

Parameters:
obj - UGeometry instance where the generated geometry should be stored
inset - Inset of the extruded face
extrusion - Extrusion factor for the the extruded face. No checking is undertaken to prevent intersections with other geometry.
isWindow - isWindow Flag indicating whether to leave front faces empty to create a window effect.
Returns:
